testcase.name: [cert-manager] CA Injector for conversion webhooks should inject a CA directly from a secret if the inject-ca-from-secret annotation is present
[Conformance] Certificates with issuer type CA Issuer should issue a certificate that defines a CommonName and URI SAN
[Conformance] Certificates with issuer type SelfSigned ClusterIssuer should issue a certificate that defines a distinct DNS Name and another distinct Common Name
[Conformance] Certificates with issuer type SelfSigned ClusterIssuer should issue a certificate that defines a DNS Name and sets a duration
[Conformance] Certificates with issuer type ACME HTTP01 ClusterIssuer should issue an ECDSA, defaulted certificate for a single distinct dnsName
[cert-manager] ACME Certificate (HTTP01) should obtain a signed ecdsa certificate with a single CN from the ACME server
[cert-manager] CA Injector for validating webhooks should inject the apiserver CA if the inject-apiserver-ca annotation is present
[cert-manager] Vault ClusterIssuer CertificateRequest (AppRole) should generate a new certificate with Vault configured maximum TTL duration (90 days) when requested duration is greater than TTL
[cert-manager] CA Certificate when the CA is an issuer should generate a signed keypair
[cert-manager] Vault Issuer Certificate (AppRole) should generate a new certificate valid for the default value (90 days)
[Conformance] Certificates with issuer type VaultAppRole Issuer should issue a certificate that defines a distinct DNS Name and another distinct Common Name
